## HTML Slide Markup

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Presentation Title</title>
  <!-- Google Fonts (choose appropriate to aesthetic) -->
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@700;900&family=Lato:wght@300;400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <!-- Icon library: pick ONE -->
  <!-- Font Awesome -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.5.1/css/all.min.css" crossorigin="anonymous" />
  <!-- OR Tabler Icons -->
  <!-- <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/@tabler/icons-webfont@latest/tabler-icons.min.css" /> -->
  <!-- OR Lucide (requires lucide.createIcons() call in script) -->
  <!-- <script src="https://unpkg.com/lucide@latest"></script> -->
  <style>/* All styles here */</style>
</head>
<body>
  <a class="back" href="../">← Back</a>

  <section class="slide active" data-slide="0"><!-- Slide 0 --></section>
  <section class="slide" data-slide="1"><!-- Slide 1 --></section>
  <!-- ... more slides ... -->

  <div class="nav">
    <button type="button" id="prev">Previous</button>
    <button type="button" id="next">Next</button>
  </div>

  <script>/* Navigation + animation triggers */</script>
</body>
</html>
```

**Slide rules:**
- First slide: `class="slide active" data-slide="0"`
- All others: `class="slide" data-slide="N"`
- Always end with a closing/thank-you slide

