## CSS Architecture

### Core Layout

```css
*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

:root {
  /* Define your palette as variables */
  --bg: #0d0d0d;
  --surface: #1a1a1a;
  --accent: #e8ff47;
  --text: #f0f0f0;
  --muted: #888;
  --font-display: 'Playfair Display', serif;
  --font-body: 'Lato', sans-serif;
}

html, body {
  height: 100%;
  overflow: hidden;
  background: var(--bg);
  color: var(--text);
  font-family: var(--font-body);
}

/* ─── Slide base ─── */
.slide {
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 4rem;
  opacity: 0;
  pointer-events: none;
  /* Default: invisible, off-screen right */
  transform: translateX(60px);
  transition: none; /* driven by animations */
}

.slide.active {
  opacity: 1;
  pointer-events: auto;
  transform: translateX(0);
  animation: slideEnter 0.55s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1) forwards;
}

.slide.leaving {
  animation: slideLeave 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.55, 0, 1, 0.45) forwards;
}

/* Direction-aware: reverse when going backwards */
[data-dir="prev"] .slide.active {
  animation: slideEnterReverse 0.55s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1) forwards;
}
[data-dir="prev"] .slide.leaving {
  animation: slideLeaveReverse 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.55, 0, 1, 0.45) forwards;
}
```

### Slide Transition Keyframes

Choose **one transition style** to match the aesthetic. Pick the most fitting:

**Option A — Horizontal Slide (clean, modern)**
```css
@keyframes slideEnter        { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateX(80px);  } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateX(0); } }
@keyframes slideLeave        { from { opacity: 1; transform: translateX(0);     } to { opacity: 0; transform: translateX(-80px); } }
@keyframes slideEnterReverse { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateX(-80px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateX(0); } }
@keyframes slideLeaveReverse { from { opacity: 1; transform: translateX(0);     } to { opacity: 0; transform: translateX(80px); } }
```

**Option B — Scale + Fade (dramatic, cinematic)**
```css
@keyframes slideEnter        { from { opacity: 0; transform: scale(0.92) translateY(20px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1) translateY(0); } }
@keyframes slideLeave        { from { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1);    } to { opacity: 0; transform: scale(1.05) translateY(-20px); } }
@keyframes slideEnterReverse { from { opacity: 0; transform: scale(1.05) translateY(-20px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1) translateY(0); } }
@keyframes slideLeaveReverse { from { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1);    } to { opacity: 0; transform: scale(0.92) translateY(20px); } }
```

**Option C — Vertical Scroll (editorial)**
```css
@keyframes slideEnter        { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(60px);  } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }
@keyframes slideLeave        { from { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0);     } to { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-60px); } }
@keyframes slideEnterReverse { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-60px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }
@keyframes slideLeaveReverse { from { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0);     } to { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(60px); } }
```

### In-Slide Content Animations

Animate slide content on entry using `animation-delay` so elements reveal in sequence:

```css
/* Stagger children on active slide */
.slide.active h1 { animation: contentIn 0.6s 0.15s cubic-bezier(0.22,1,0.36,1) both; }
.slide.active h2 { animation: contentIn 0.6s 0.25s cubic-bezier(0.22,1,0.36,1) both; }
.slide.active p  { animation: contentIn 0.6s 0.35s cubic-bezier(0.22,1,0.36,1) both; }
.slide.active ul { animation: contentIn 0.6s 0.4s  cubic-bezier(0.22,1,0.36,1) both; }

/* Stagger individual list items */
.slide.active li:nth-child(1) { animation: contentIn 0.5s 0.45s both; }
.slide.active li:nth-child(2) { animation: contentIn 0.5s 0.55s both; }
.slide.active li:nth-child(3) { animation: contentIn 0.5s 0.65s both; }
.slide.active li:nth-child(4) { animation: contentIn 0.5s 0.75s both; }

@keyframes contentIn {
  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(24px); }
  to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}
```

