## Visual Techniques & Effects Catalog

Use these to make slides extraordinary. Mix and match based on the aesthetic:

### Backgrounds

```css
/* Gradient mesh (soft, modern) */
background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 20% 50%, #1a0533 0%, transparent 60%),
            radial-gradient(ellipse at 80% 20%, #0d2b45 0%, transparent 60%),
            #080810;

/* Noise texture overlay (add depth) */
.slide::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 200 200' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='n'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.65' numOctaves='3' /%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100%25' height='100%25' filter='url(%23n)' opacity='0.04'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
  opacity: 0.3;
  pointer-events: none;
}

/* Animated gradient (breathing, alive) */
@keyframes gradientShift {
  0%, 100% { background-position: 0% 50%; }
  50%       { background-position: 100% 50%; }
}
.slide {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d0221, #1a0a2e, #0d1b2a);
  background-size: 300% 300%;
  animation: gradientShift 8s ease infinite;
}

/* Geometric grid lines */
.slide::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background-image:
    linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.03) 1px, transparent 1px),
    linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.03) 1px, transparent 1px);
  background-size: 60px 60px;
  pointer-events: none;
}
```

