## Quality Checklist

Before finishing, verify:

- [ ] **Distinct identity**: Does this look like it was designed specifically for this topic, not a generic template?
- [ ] **Typography**: Custom Google Fonts loaded, NOT Arial/Roboto/Inter
- [ ] **Color palette**: CSS variables defined, 3–5 colors, bold accent
- [ ] **Slide transitions**: Direction-aware enter/leave animations implemented
- [ ] **Content animations**: Staggered reveals on headings, paragraphs, list items
- [ ] **Icons**: At least one icon library included and used meaningfully
- [ ] **Nav**: Keyboard (Arrow keys, Space) + button navigation works
- [ ] **Back link**: Present, top-left, styled subtly
- [ ] **Closing slide**: Final thank-you or CTA slide included
- [ ] **Self-contained**: No external dependencies other than CDN links; single HTML file
- [ ] **Memorable detail**: One signature effect that makes this presentation unforgettable
- [ ] **Root index.html updated** (if in a multi-deck repo)

---

## Anti-Patterns — Never Do These

- ❌ Use Arial, Roboto, Inter, or system-ui as the main font
- ❌ Purple gradient on white background (default AI aesthetic)
- ❌ Flat, static slides with no animation or motion
- ❌ More than ~6 bullet points on a single slide
- ❌ Emoji as icons (use a proper icon library)
- ❌ Hardcoded colors scattered throughout CSS (use CSS variables)
- ❌ Slides that look like Word documents
- ❌ Generic "Thank You" on a plain white background for the last slide
- ❌ Identical slide layouts repeated throughout the deck with no visual variation

